HEADWORD: mellowed
<hw>mellowed</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>having a mild and
pleasing flavor through proper aging.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> mellow.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>having attained to kindliness or gentleness through
age and experience; -- of people.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> gentle, mellow.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>mellowing</ent>⟦br⟧
